text.section:
The fiscal court of each county is hereby given the authority to impose with respect:
To each restaurant serving meals, a license fee not to exceed ten dollars ($10) per annum;
To each retail outlet of soft drinks or ice cream, a license fee not to exceed five dollars ($5) per annum. In cases where ice cream and soft drinks are sold by the same retail outlet, one (1) license tax not to exceed ten dollars ($10) per annum;
To each billiard or pool table or bowling alley, irrespective of size, where a fee is charged and collected, directly or indirectly, a license fee not to exceed thirty dollars ($30) per annum for the first table or alley and not to exceed five dollars ($5) per annum for each additional table or alley;
To each place where tobacco products are sold at retail, a license fee not to exceed ten dollars ($10) per annum.
